# Testing your in-person verification service with the GOV.UK Wallet Sandbox

The GOV.UK Wallet Sandbox will let you create a test digital driving licence and save it to your GOV.UK Wallet test app. You can then present the test digital driving licence to your in-person verification service and confirm it can [receive credential information](/verify-credentials). You will be able to complete this flow on Android and iOS devices.

The GOV.UK Wallet Sandbox will contain:

- a [document builder](#using-the-gov-uk-wallet-sandbox-document-builder) that lets you issue a credential offer for a test digital driving licence
- a GOV.UK Wallet test app that lets you store and share a test digital driving licence
- a [mock Status List Service](#using-the-sandbox-mock-status-list) that lets you revoke or check the status of your test digital driving licence
- a certificate authority that provides a certificate that authenticates you when connecting to the GOV.UK Wallet test app

You must not use the GOV.UK Wallet Sandbox tools in your production environment or as part of your live deployment process. The tools are limited to validating the integration with your verification service, and can not be used to test all credential types and attributes. You must write and maintain your own test suite in addition to the GOV.UK Wallet Sandbox tools.

## Before you use the GOV.UK Wallet Sandbox

To use the GOV.UK Wallet Sandbox, you must:

- complete the enrolment process to become a certified Digital Verification Services (DVS) provider on the [digital identity and attribute services register](https://www.digital-identity-services-register.service.gov.uk/)
- have been given access to our verifier test tools (for example, TestFlight or Google Play Console) and installed these on your device
- have received an integration certificate from the GOV.UK Wallet team

If you have not completed these steps, speak to your GOV.UK Wallet engagement manager or [contact us](contact-us).

## Using the GOV.UK Wallet Sandbox document builder

You can use the document builder to:

- [issue a new test digital driving licence](#issue-a-test-digital-driving-licence)
- [revoke an issued test digital driving licence](#revoke-a-test-digital-driving-licence)

You should use the test digital driving licence to validate the end-to-end journey of your verification service.

### Issue a new test digital driving licence

1. Open the [sandbox document builder](https://stub-credential-issuer.wallet-onboarding.integration.account.gov.uk/dvs/start) in your web browser. 

1. Click "Start now".

1. Choose "Issue a new test digital driving licence" and click "Continue" - the document builder will issue a new credential offer for a test digital driving licence.

You should use this credential offer to add the test digital driving licence to your GOV.UK Wallet test app by:

- choosing the "Add document" button if the document builder is on the same smartphone as the GOV.UK Wallet test app
- using the device with the GOV.UK Wallet test app to scan the QR code if the document builder is on a different device

The test digital driving licence will have:

- a unique driving licence number in the format `TST-{TIMESTAMP}`, where the timestamp is in epoch milliseconds
- a credential issuer of "GDS"

When the test digital driving licence is added to your GOV.UK Wallet test app, you can begin using it to test your verification service.

### Revoke a test digital driving licence

Credential issuers can [revoke a credential](/issue-credentials/status-list/revoke-credential) they have issued. Your verification service must recognise when a credential has been revoked by the issuer and must cancel the verification flow.

The document builder allows you to revoke a test digital driving licence you have previously issued. This helps you test your verification service responds correctly when an issuer revokes a credential.

When you open the GOV.UK Wallet test app, the app will check the status of its credentials and will invalidate any revoked driving licences. Before you test your revoked credential flow, you should set the device with your GOV.UK Wallet test app to airplane mode to prevent this behaviour. If the GOV.UK Wallet test app invalidates your test digital driving licence, you must issue and revoke a new one. 

To revoke a test digital driving licence:

1. Set the device with your GOV.UK Wallet test app to airplane mode.

1. Make a note of the test digital driving licence number you want to revoke. 

1. Access the [sandbox document builder](https://stub-credential-issuer.wallet-onboarding.integration.account.gov.uk/dvs/start).  

1. Choose "Revoke an issued test digital driving licence" and click Continue.

1. Enter the test digital driving licence number you want to revoke. 

